{
  "texts": [
    "Our model is trained on pre-extracted features using this backbone.",
    "Five frame features for each segment are uniformly selected and fed to a linear layer, followed by a ReLU activation and dropout with probability 0.5.",
    "Frame features are temporally aggregated using a TRN (Zhou et al., 2018) mod-) and dark colors denote source and target validation domains, respectively.",
    "a In the \"Source Only\" setting, different modalities and domains result in unbalanced feature norms.",
    "b L RNA in DG improves the alignment between different modalities, but leaves a gap between the source and target domains."
  ]
}